    "review::.::holistic::cross_module_architecture::parallel_realtime_stacks::8eae5370": {
      "id": "review::.::holistic::cross_module_architecture::parallel_realtime_stacks::8eae5370",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 3,
      "confidence": "medium",
      "summary": "Two parallel realtime/command architectures coexist (compiled websocket hub vs runtime command+transport modules), creating duplicated boundaries and drift risk.",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "cross_module_architecture",
        "related_files": [
          "goseg/web/_app/immutable/chunks/websocket.84e20bf3.js",
          "ui/src/lib/runtime/commands/system-commands.js",
          "ui/src/lib/runtime/commands/ship-commands.js",
          "ui/src/lib/runtime/transport/websocket-client.js",
          "ui/src/lib/stores/logsocket.js"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "Compiled websocket chunk defines many command payload constructors (`{type:\"system\",action:\"groundseg\",command:\"restart\"}`, `{type:\"system\",action:\"wifi-connect\",...}`, `{type:\"pier_upload\",...}`, `{type:\"new_ship\",...}`), while runtime commands modules define overlapping command intents via `sendSystemCommand` and `sendActionCommand`.",
          "`ui/src/lib/stores/logsocket.js` introduces a separate runtime websocket client and token-loading flow (`createWebSocketClient`, `loadSession`) instead of sharing one realtime service boundary with the compiled path.",
          "This duplicate command/transport surface means policy changes (validation, retries, auth shape) can diverge between stacks."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Converge to a single runtime command and realtime service layer, then make generated/entry code consume that layer through stable adapters. Eliminate duplicated command-shape ownership from transport modules.",
        "reasoning": ""
      },
      "status": "auto_resolved",
      "note": "Disappeared from scan \u2014 likely fixed",
      "first_seen": "2026-03-01T08:35:44+00:00",
